> [{quoted}](name=Meddler,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=kjjEEb2Q,comment-id=00000001,timestamp=2015-06-03T04:09:55.823+0000)
>Ashe by contrast's distinguished from other ADCs most by the sheer amount of CC she brings. 

Haha, that's cute. {{champion:110}}

@RIOT Meddler
The problem here is, an ADC regardless of their Kit is an ADC. they are supposed to be able to clear a lane, kill a tower and deal a large amount of damage at the cost of utility and defense. if you make an ADC with a basis built on utility ("the sheer amount of CC she brings") then you are creating an AD based support and not a true ADC.

That being said; make her auto attack slow higher, say 40%. then make it only apply every 3 seconds or something. that way she cant perma slow someone but you can leave her damage (what an ADC does) alone.

